# Cloudflare Pages — URL rewrites.
#
# /admin/ is a single-page app: one HTML file at /admin/index.html,
# JS routes between views by reading window.location.pathname. Without
# rewrites, navigating directly to /admin/bookings/ would 404 because
# there's no /admin/bookings/index.html on disk.
#
# The obvious rule — `/admin/*  /admin/index.html  200` — gets dropped
# by Cloudflare's loop detector ("destination /admin/index.html
# canonicalises to /admin/, which matches the source /admin/*"). To
# avoid that we enumerate the routes explicitly: each source is a
# specific path that can't canonicalise back into another rule.
#
# The bare /admin/ path doesn't need a rule — Cloudflare Pages serves
# /admin/index.html automatically as the directory index.
#
# When you add a new sidebar route in admin/index.html, add the
# corresponding rule pair (with and without trailing slash) below.

/admin/bookings   /admin/index.html  200
/admin/bookings/  /admin/index.html  200
/admin/hotels     /admin/index.html  200
/admin/hotels/    /admin/index.html  200
/admin/tours      /admin/index.html  200
/admin/tours/     /admin/index.html  200
/admin/payments   /admin/index.html  200
/admin/payments/  /admin/index.html  200
/admin/billing    /admin/index.html  200
/admin/billing/   /admin/index.html  200
/admin/invoices   /admin/index.html  200
/admin/invoices/  /admin/index.html  200
